<br>
First of all, I'm on Rallos Zek, too. I originally came from Innoruuk, where I have a 49 Druid, but I found blue servers and Druids to be a big bore (and complete crap in high-end stuff) so I moved to Rallos.<br>
<br>
First and foremost, as a newbie, from 6 to around 20, YOU WILL BE PKED LIKE HELL! Learn to bag quickly, and get as much DECENT no-drop as you can. Meaning no crappy Reserve Militia Tunics and such. But since you're a monk, I can't think of much easy stuff to get, so I can't help you there.<br>
<br>
As for PVP, monks aren't a very good choice. Your gear is limited, although that also means you won't lose as much AC than other classes by switching to resist gear. (of course, a lot of armors that monks can't wear give resists too) Not to mention, being a pure melee that doesn't have a huge damaging attack (backstab) or a stun attack (bash/slam), you're disadvantaged again. I hope you have a fast connection, and learn how to circle-strafe quickly, otherwise you'll never last. That, or learn to run like hell and jump in water before people can get their spells off. (land casting into water doesn't work, and vice versa. Both gotta be on land or in water)<br>
<br>
You ask about equipment: This isn't a damn blue server, accept that. I don't want to be mean but seriously, deal with it. Once you get past 20, and you're in a group you can trust, you can gear up. Or if you're in a VERY unpopulated zone, and are sure no PKs are in the zone, gear up and solo (if you can). Otherwise, your arse is going to be bare. (My Shadow Knight very rarely puts on his gear, but he has a lot of Royal Velium Frosted armor...)<br>
<br>
